---
/**
 * Problem-framing section. Three vignettes — one per pillar — that
 * each name a pain the reader feels, then explain what CTXone does
 * about it. The mapping is:
 *
 *   Stateful     → yesterday's context vanished
 *   Sharable     → your teammate is flying blind
 *   Inspectable  → who told the model that? no one remembers
 *
 * Each vignette is a personal story, not a feature bullet. That's
 * the whole point — this is a dev tool but the reader is human.
 */
---

<section class="section problem">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">
			<span class="dot"></span>
			<span class="eyebrow-text">CONTEXT_ANXIETY.md</span>
		</div>
		<h2 class="section-title">Three flavors of context anxiety.</h2>
		<p class="section-lede">
			Everyone using AI coding tools feels all three, even if
			they've never named them. CTXone's three pillars map
			one-to-one to the three versions of the pain.
		</p>

		<div class="vignettes">
			<article class="vignette v-stateful">
				<div class="v-label">01 // STATEFUL</div>
				<h3>Yesterday's context is gone.</h3>
				<p class="scene">
					You told Claude on Tuesday that you're using
					SQLite, not Postgres, and why. Wednesday morning
					you open a new chat and it's asking about your
					"Postgres schema" again. You paste the same
					paragraph. You budget tokens for memory the model
					should already have.
				</p>
				<p class="fix">
					<strong>CTXone remembers.</strong> Every fact
					survives sessions, branches, and tool switches
					because it's stored in a local graph, not in the
					model's context window.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="vignette v-sharable">
				<div class="v-label">02 // SHARABLE</div>
				<h3>Your teammate is flying blind.</h3>
				<p class="scene">
					You primed your Cursor install with the team's
					architectural decisions. Priya didn't. Now she's
					arguing with the model about whether to use Redis
					for the job queue — a question you settled three
					months ago in Slack and she never saw.
				</p>
				<p class="fix">
					<strong>CTXone is shared.</strong> The graph is a
					file. Commit it, sync it, mount it over the team's
					lab network. Whatever you primed is what everyone
					else sees.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="vignette v-inspectable">
				<div class="v-label">03 // INSPECTABLE</div>
				<h3>Who told the model that?</h3>
				<p class="scene">
					You open a file Claude edited last week and there's
					a comment about "the new API versioning policy."
					You don't remember a policy. Nobody on the team
					remembers a policy. Did the model hallucinate it?
					Did you mention it once in a side chat? Nobody can
					check. The decision is orphaned.
				</p>
				<p class="fix">
					<strong>CTXone is accountable.</strong> Every
					commit carries an agent ID, a timestamp, an intent,
					and reasoning. <code>ctx blame</code> shows you
					exactly who wrote what, when, and why — git-style.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>

		<p class="read-more">
			<a href="/why-ctxone/context-anxiety/">
				Read the full context anxiety argument →
			</a>
		</p>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.problem {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 50% 40% at 20% 0%,
				rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.05),
				transparent 60%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(252, 211, 77, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(252, 211, 77, 0.25);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.eyebrow .dot {
		width: 6px;
		height: 6px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--ctx-warn);
	}

	.eyebrow-text {
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.vignettes {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.vignette {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.vignette::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 0;
		bottom: 0;
		width: 3px;
	}

	.v-stateful::before {
		background: var(--ctx-accent);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.5);
	}

	.v-sharable::before {
		background: var(--ctx-success);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.5);
	}

	.v-inspectable::before {
		background: var(--ctx-warn);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(252, 211, 77, 0.5);
	}

	.v-label {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.v-stateful .v-label {
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
	}

	.v-sharable .v-label {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
	}

	.v-inspectable .v-label {
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
	}

	.vignette h3 {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
		line-height: 1.25;
	}

	.scene {
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
	}

	.fix {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		line-height: 1.55;
		margin: 0;
		padding-top: 0.85rem;
		border-top: 1px dashed var(--ctx-border);
	}

	.fix strong {
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	.fix code {
		background: #050505;
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
		padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		font-size: 0.9em;
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.read-more {
		margin: 2rem 0 0 0;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 920px) {
		.vignettes {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
